WEBVTT

00:04.994 --> 00:06.216
Hey, this is Stephen Furtick.

00:06.256 --> 00:09.361
I'm the pastor of Elevation Church, and this is our podcast.

00:09.481 --> 00:13.729
Be sure to subscribe so we can get you these new sermons every week.

00:14.009 --> 00:14.951
Hope you're blessed today.

00:21.121 --> 00:22.704
Slipped our hands together for a moment.

00:22.724 --> 00:28.413
Let's have a prayer of consecration as we head into a new year together as a church family.

00:30.637 --> 00:31.378
Jesus.

00:33.186 --> 00:36.050
It's your name we exalt today, we exalt you in our lives.

00:37.572 --> 00:44.822
As we head into a new year, we just re-establish in our own hearts today that Jesus, you are our priority.

00:45.984 --> 00:47.466
You are our desire.

00:48.407 --> 00:50.130
You are our one ambition.

00:51.572 --> 00:58.802
I don't know what this year holds, whether it's hills, whether it's valleys, but I know that you go with me and that you go before me.

00:59.842 --> 01:04.290
Once we head into this new year, we thank you, God, that all the weapons might be formed against us.

01:04.390 --> 01:06.794
They will not prosper or prevail.

01:07.415 --> 01:17.974
I thank you that surely goodness and mercy will follow me all the days of my life, and I will dwell in the house of the Lord forever.

01:18.114 --> 01:20.178
Thank you for your abiding presence.

01:20.386 --> 01:22.088
Thank you for your strength this year.

01:22.348 --> 01:26.173
Thank you for a spirit of perseverance falling on your people, God.

01:26.233 --> 01:30.698
Thank you, Lord, that as we orient our hearts towards you, we will see your kingdom come.

01:31.239 --> 01:35.164
Your will be done here on earth as it is in heaven.

01:35.624 --> 01:36.686
We honor you, Lord.

01:37.206 --> 01:38.167
We give you our hearts.

01:38.788 --> 01:39.749
We give you our lives.

01:40.290 --> 01:41.551
It's in your name we pray.

01:42.533 --> 01:42.953
Amen.

01:42.993 --> 01:44.335
Amen.

01:48.780 --> 01:50.322
Well, happy new year, everybody.

01:51.298 --> 01:53.661
It feels good to start out the year and worship, doesn't it?

01:55.162 --> 01:57.305
If I haven't got a chance to meet you, my name is Jonathan.

01:57.325 --> 01:59.648
I know we have so many new people here today.

01:59.728 --> 02:00.388
My name is Jonathan.

02:00.408 --> 02:01.530
I'm one of the pastors here.

02:02.030 --> 02:04.473
Let me show you a picture of my family real quick.

02:04.573 --> 02:05.314
I'll throw it up there.

02:05.334 --> 02:07.917
It's my wife, Anna, and our three kids.

02:10.941 --> 02:13.764
We've been a part of this church for 13 years now.

02:14.565 --> 02:19.250
For us, it's such a joy to be able to be a part of this church family, this church community.

02:19.330 --> 02:21.913
to be under the incredible leadership of our pastor.

02:21.933 --> 02:24.095
Can we thank the Lord for our pastor?

02:28.180 --> 02:35.308
You know, not too long ago, after I preached recently, someone came up to me and they said, man, I really enjoyed the sermon you preached.

02:35.328 --> 02:36.329
I said, thank you so much.

02:36.550 --> 02:40.694
And then what they said next, they said it like it was the big accomplishment.

02:40.714 --> 02:44.979
They said, you know, I used to get so upset when pastor Stephen wasn't preaching.

02:45.760 --> 02:47.442
And they said, but now I've decided

02:47.554 --> 02:50.999
When he's not preaching, I'm just gonna thank God that he's getting to rest his voice.

02:52.320 --> 02:55.424
And I didn't really know how to take that, but let's get in on it together.

02:55.445 --> 02:59.290
And let's thank God that our pastor's getting to rest his voice this weekend.

03:00.311 --> 03:00.912
Who are we kidding?

03:00.932 --> 03:10.925
He's probably writing a brand new song for us to sing right now, but I'm really excited about what the Lord has given me to share with you today on the cusp of this new year.

03:11.105 --> 03:14.610
And we're gonna look at a scripture from Acts 3 that I think

03:15.202 --> 03:18.466
Has several implications for us today, but we'll also set the tone for us.

03:18.486 --> 03:19.507
We're going to read our scripture.

03:19.527 --> 03:23.532
You can stay standing for just a moment and then we'll get to sit down after that.

03:23.572 --> 03:24.453
It's optional, but.

03:26.596 --> 03:27.377
Acts chapter three.

03:29.259 --> 03:30.781
One day, everybody say one day.

03:30.801 --> 03:35.086
I won't have you repeat every two words, but just a few along the way.

03:35.126 --> 03:36.107
Everyone say one day.

03:36.147 --> 03:41.814
Peter and John were going up to the temple at the time of prayer at three in the afternoon.

03:42.555 --> 03:44.818
Now a man who was lame from birth.

03:45.218 --> 03:52.846
was being carried to the temple gate called Beautiful, where he was put every day to beg from those going into the temple courts.

03:54.467 --> 03:58.151
When he saw Peter and John about the enter, he asked them for money.

03:58.872 --> 04:02.075
Peter looked straight at him, as did John.

04:02.716 --> 04:04.718
Then Peter said, look at us.

04:05.779 --> 04:11.865
So the man gave them his attention, expecting to get something from them.

04:11.905 --> 04:13.106
Everyone say, expecting.

04:15.234 --> 04:19.641
Then Peter said, silver or gold I do not have, but what I do have, I give you.

04:20.323 --> 04:24.409
In the name of Jesus Christ of Nazareth, walk.

04:25.311 --> 04:32.202
Taking him by the right hand, he helped him up, and instantly the man's feet and ankles became strong.

04:32.944 --> 04:35.448
He jumped to his feet, and he began to walk.

04:35.969 --> 04:39.154
Then he went with them into the temple courts, walking

04:39.266 --> 04:46.192
and jumping and praising God that anyone walking to church like that today, walking and jumping and praising God.

04:49.335 --> 04:58.904
When all the people saw him walking and praising God, they recognized him as the same man who used to sit begging at the temple gate called Beautiful.

04:59.445 --> 05:04.890
And they were filled with wonder and amazement at what had happened to him.

05:05.811 --> 05:09.234
My title for today is expecting change.

05:10.018 --> 05:12.420
expecting change, go ahead and grab a seat.

05:16.284 --> 05:20.148
I thought that would be a good title for your first Sunday of a new year.

05:20.288 --> 05:22.971
Anyone expecting change going into this year?

05:23.692 --> 05:30.839
Now, I know that there's probably 60% of you that when it comes to a new year, you roll your eyes at the thought of New Year's resolutions.

05:30.859 --> 05:37.586
You're like, it's January 4th and already most people have already failed at the things that they set out to do this year.

05:37.794 --> 05:40.237
This is not a New Year's resolution message, don't worry.

05:40.277 --> 05:44.603
Even though there's others of you who, I mean, this is like your favorite time of the year.

05:44.643 --> 05:54.075
You've already had an off site with your spouse, you've reflected on the prior year, you've set your budget, all your vacations planned, every date night, all your workouts, you've got it all locked in.

05:54.095 --> 05:58.720
Anybody like that, you're just so excited for a new year in the possibility of change, no one?

05:59.201 --> 06:02.065
Okay, cool, we're talking to a cynical church today, that's amazing.

06:02.705 --> 06:03.186
Okay.

06:03.970 --> 06:11.681
But there is, even though I know there's a part of us that goes, what's so different about December 31st to January 1st?

06:11.701 --> 06:13.124
It's just a change on the calendar.

06:13.204 --> 06:23.619
And yet, there's something about transitions in our life that create a sense of expectation or even anticipation for change to happen in our life.

06:23.759 --> 06:29.267
Often, God will use external transition to bring about internal change in our lives.

06:29.287 --> 06:33.714
So even though you're heading into a new year and some of your, I don't know what's going to be different from this year,

06:33.858 --> 06:43.069
Next, there is a sense of optimism, let's say, in the atmosphere even today that maybe something could be different as we head into a new year.

06:43.530 --> 06:46.153
Now, New Year's resolutions, that's one thing.

06:46.193 --> 06:49.497
If you're trying to lose weight this year or set up an emergency fund, that's amazing.

06:49.517 --> 06:51.720
You can come up with your plan and set your goals.

06:51.780 --> 07:03.154
But what I want to talk to you about today is less about those type of changes that you need to see happen in your life and that you want to work towards this year.

07:03.362 --> 07:08.509
I want to talk to you more so about the God changes that you need to see happen in your life.

07:09.670 --> 07:14.416
As we ended last year, many people in our church participated in our year on offering.

07:14.496 --> 07:18.582
Once again, thank you to everyone who is a part of our trust in God offering this year.

07:20.544 --> 07:28.114
And as part of that process, we ask everyone in our church to write down a word that represents what they're believing God for as we head into a new year.

07:28.514 --> 07:33.821
And as our staff was praying over those words, there wasn't a single word that I saw that looked like a New Year's resolution.

07:34.301 --> 07:37.005
I didn't see, go to the gym, eat more vegetables.

07:38.306 --> 07:40.169
I saw words like restoration.

07:41.030 --> 07:42.291
I saw words like healing.

07:42.332 --> 07:44.975
I saw words like forgiveness.

07:45.055 --> 07:46.637
These aren't ordinary changes.

07:46.697 --> 07:48.179
These are God changes.

07:48.239 --> 07:53.746
These are things that can only happen in our life when God begins to create change in us.

07:54.242 --> 08:05.648
So I love the story of this man in Acts and I was drawn to it because on this ordinary day, remember Luke starts out Luke who wrote the book of Acts and the gospel of Luke.

08:05.668 --> 08:08.274
Starts off by painting this as just a day

08:08.386 --> 08:09.327
like any other day.

08:09.407 --> 08:11.009
This is not December 31st.

08:11.069 --> 08:12.471
This is not January 1st.

08:12.491 --> 08:13.653
This is not Peter's birthday.

08:13.673 --> 08:14.814
This is not the man's birthday.

08:14.854 --> 08:15.535
It's not Christmas.

08:15.595 --> 08:16.577
It's not Easter.

08:16.597 --> 08:17.918
It's an ordinary day.

08:18.339 --> 08:22.664
And yet something extraordinary happens in the middle of an ordinary day.

08:22.684 --> 08:26.950
How many believe that God can do something extraordinary on an ordinary day?

08:29.233 --> 08:30.194
Everything about

08:30.498 --> 08:33.641
His language is indicating that there's nothing special about today.

08:33.701 --> 08:36.304
One day, Peter and John are going to the temple.

08:36.324 --> 08:37.665
They're going at the time of prayer.

08:37.705 --> 08:39.126
This would have been part of their custom.

08:39.146 --> 08:40.688
This is just what they do.

08:40.768 --> 08:47.514
And then it tells us that there is a man who every day, every day, was put out by the temple gates to beg for money.

08:47.654 --> 08:52.659
It's an ordinary day and yet something so profound happens to this man on this day.

08:52.960 --> 08:54.121
This man who was lame.

08:54.541 --> 08:59.666
Luke later tells us that he was about 40 years old, but all his life, this was his routine.

08:59.810 --> 09:08.625
wake up in the morning, and I don't know who took him to the gates, whether it was his parents or whether it's for his friends, but someone took him and set him outside that gate.

09:09.066 --> 09:11.591
And day after day, he would sit there and beg for money.

09:11.691 --> 09:16.719
And yet something happens on this day that changed this man's life forever.

09:17.661 --> 09:25.074
Now, when you come to church, it's so important that you come in with a level of expectation that God could do something in your life today.

09:25.890 --> 09:29.037
Sometimes we get in the habit of treating it like, oh, it's just another Sunday.

09:29.057 --> 09:30.440
I'm going to hear some worship songs.

09:30.501 --> 09:31.463
I'm going to hear a message.

09:31.503 --> 09:39.541
But what if you came in with the expectation and belief that today God could do something in your life that would change you for the rest of your life?

09:40.082 --> 09:43.410
Anybody believe that anything is possible with God today?

09:47.842 --> 10:06.851
Now, as I read about this man's miracle, the question and the tension for me of why I kept going back to this passage is I think it's so amazing that as he meets Peter and he meets John and that his legs are strengthened and he jumps and he leaps and he praises God, I want to celebrate the miracle that happened in his life, but the question that brings up in me is why now?

10:08.574 --> 10:13.562
After 40 years of waking up day after day, why now?

10:15.064 --> 10:16.466
Why did God choose to heal him?

10:16.642 --> 10:17.243
this day.

10:17.643 --> 10:19.967
Even pastorally, I wonder that a lot.

10:20.307 --> 10:23.732
It's amazing what I get to see God do in the lives of the people of this church.

10:23.752 --> 10:30.401
And when someone lets me know that, God set them free from PTSD or God set them free from a pornography addiction.

10:30.681 --> 10:33.685
I'm the first one to celebrate and praise God for what he's done.

10:33.705 --> 10:42.537
When someone tells me how God completely restored their marriage after all kinds of betrayal, I want to praise God, jump leap, praise God with them for what he's done.

10:42.597 --> 10:46.002
But in the back of my mind sometimes, I'm asking the question,

10:46.210 --> 10:46.751
Why now?

10:47.712 --> 10:57.825
And maybe you found yourself in that place too, where you're like, God, I'm so thankful after all these years of being single, you finally brought a man into my life, but God, why now?

10:58.706 --> 10:59.167
Why now?

10:59.687 --> 11:01.129
What was it about today?

11:01.189 --> 11:06.076
What was it about this one day that led to this man being changed?

11:06.096 --> 11:07.357
And so look at this story with me.

11:07.758 --> 11:12.884
It says, day after day, every day he was put out the temple to beg from those going into the temple courts.

11:12.904 --> 11:14.226
And he sees Peter and John,

11:14.690 --> 11:16.052
And he asked them for money.

11:16.172 --> 11:17.754
Peter looks at him as did John.

11:18.294 --> 11:19.456
And look at this in verse five.

11:19.516 --> 11:25.243
So the man gave them his attention expecting to get something from them.

11:25.864 --> 11:28.267
But he's not expecting a healing that day.

11:28.927 --> 11:30.369
He's just expecting some money.

11:30.429 --> 11:32.572
He's just expecting change.

11:33.433 --> 11:37.057
And yet what he got was so much greater than even what he was expecting.

11:37.077 --> 11:42.704
Now, I wonder if there is ever a point in this man's life where he was expecting a miracle.

11:43.345 --> 11:44.306
It wasn't this day.

11:44.706 --> 11:52.678
But I wonder maybe if in his teenage years he had days where he would just wake up in the morning and try to wiggle his toes wondering maybe things will be different for me today.

11:53.759 --> 11:57.084
Maybe today I won't have to call my friends and ask them to take me to the gate.

11:57.505 --> 12:09.543
But some of us get stuck in a condition for so long that it becomes our reality in such a way that when it comes to our relationship with God, we've even given up on expecting anything to change.

12:10.364 --> 12:14.450
And yet I'm so thankful that God is a God who exceeds

12:14.818 --> 12:15.819
our expectations.

12:17.081 --> 12:22.549
There is this phrase I picked up somewhere that I used to say that God will often meet you at the level of your expectation.

12:23.270 --> 12:35.186
And I would love to say that coming into church because on one hand it means that if I come into church just expecting it to be an ordinary day or the message was okay, then often that's what I'll experience.

12:35.522 --> 12:38.646
And so it's like God will often meet you at the level of your expectation.

12:38.666 --> 12:47.275
If you come into church with an open heart and an open mind, if you come in expecting that through the Holy Spirit, God will speak to you, often that's the very thing you receive.

12:48.136 --> 12:50.799
And yet when I think about that statement, I couldn't be more wrong.

12:51.360 --> 12:57.046
Because when I look back over my life, I'm so grateful that God did not meet me at the level of my expectation.

12:57.507 --> 13:03.794
I'm so grateful that time and time again, God has done exceedingly more than I could ever ask

13:04.066 --> 13:04.947
or imagine.

13:05.067 --> 13:06.409
Is that anyone's testimony?

13:06.830 --> 13:09.773
Like you didn't expect to even be alive today.

13:10.114 --> 13:12.036
You didn't expect to be where you are.

13:12.056 --> 13:15.761
You didn't expect to be blessed with this family, blessed with this purpose.

13:15.961 --> 13:18.965
You certainly didn't expect that you would be in church in 2026.

13:19.526 --> 13:24.693
But how many you want to praise God that he did more than you could ever expect or imagine.

13:28.538 --> 13:31.762
So he's expecting to get some change from them and instead,

13:31.874 --> 13:36.041
Peter speaks to him and it's so swaggy the way Peter does it in the name of Jesus.

13:36.742 --> 13:38.004
Get up and walk.

13:38.605 --> 13:44.714
And look at this, taking him by the right hand, he jumped up and instantly the man's feet and ankles became strong.

13:45.155 --> 13:47.018
He jumped to his feet and he began to walk.

13:47.359 --> 13:48.060
And this is key.

13:48.180 --> 13:52.006
It says that he went with them into the temple courts.

13:52.707 --> 13:59.538
That's a key detail because all his life, he was not allowed to go into the temple.

14:00.706 --> 14:06.936
Every single day of his 40 years, he was sat down outside of the temple gates.

14:07.497 --> 14:12.264
His condition prohibited him from going into the temple.

14:12.885 --> 14:22.280
And yet when God heals his condition that day, not only does he jump and walk and praise God, but it says that he went into the temple.

14:23.081 --> 14:28.690
I want you to know that when God brings about a change in your life, it's not just to fix you, it's to restore you.

14:30.338 --> 14:39.446
Because him going into the temple is significant because it represents him being restored to worship with God and restored into community with others.

14:39.846 --> 14:51.737
The things that God wants to bring in your life, the changes that God wants to do on a deep level, they're not just meant to fix your condition to make you feel better or to alleviate your pain temporarily.

14:51.977 --> 14:56.100
They're meant to restore you in worship and restore you in community.

14:56.381 --> 14:59.003
That's this most significant change that happens to this man.

14:59.023 --> 15:00.324
He goes into the temple

15:00.304 --> 15:07.861
And as he's in there, everybody recognized him as the man who looked at this, used to sit at the gate called beautiful.

15:08.883 --> 15:12.050
I love that language because, y'all, this just happened to him.

15:13.186 --> 15:16.750
This just happened to him, and yet they're already calling him the man who used to sit.

15:17.050 --> 15:23.417
That's like you introducing your husband to someone in the lobby after church and say, oh, this is Frank who used to have road rage.

15:23.437 --> 15:25.279
And they're like, what are you talking about?

15:25.299 --> 15:28.222
I just saw him getting angry in the parking lot on the way in.

15:28.262 --> 15:29.423
It wasn't all that long ago.

15:29.443 --> 15:30.004
No, no, no.

15:30.144 --> 15:31.265
He used to have road rage.

15:31.285 --> 15:37.552
He's a changed man because he was in church and God touched him and he changed the man who used to sit.

15:37.792 --> 15:39.634
And they're filled with wonder.

15:39.810 --> 15:42.113
and amazement because they recognize them.

15:42.373 --> 15:46.519
This guy for 40 years has been sitting at this gate, and isn't that the same guy?

15:46.840 --> 15:53.328
Now he's walking, he's leaping, he's jumping, he's praising God, and they're filled with wonder and amazement.

15:53.368 --> 15:57.093
Look what God does in their life because of what he's done in this man's life.

15:58.015 --> 16:02.921
God heals him, but he fills them with wonder and amazement.

16:03.182 --> 16:07.688
When a God change happens in your life, it creates wonder and other people.

16:07.948 --> 16:09.330
If it's possible for him,

16:09.538 --> 16:12.062
I wonder what God could do for me.

16:12.102 --> 16:23.860
And they're filled with wonder and amazement because, look at that, this man who had just been sitting there, instantly his feet and ankles became strong, instantly.

16:25.082 --> 16:32.513
And as I thought about that word, I thought, man, it must have been so amazing for everyone to see this man who had just been sitting their lame, suddenly walking.

16:33.895 --> 16:38.482
And yet for this man, this miracle is anything but sudden.

16:40.002 --> 16:41.164
It's been 40 years.

16:42.646 --> 16:46.712
And often the God changes that happen in your life will look sudden to other people.

16:47.634 --> 16:54.784
But for you, I mean, you know all the labor and all the prayer and all the tears you cried to get to this place.

16:54.804 --> 16:57.609
And so other people are filled with wonder and amazement.

16:57.629 --> 17:01.234
Look what God has done in your life and it looks so easy to them.

17:01.666 --> 17:07.352
And yet you know all the petitions when you went before God saying, God, can you do something about my situation?

17:07.412 --> 17:09.074
God, can you help me right now?

17:09.375 --> 17:13.139
And so it was sudden to them, but it was slow to him.

17:13.880 --> 17:16.683
And it brought back up that question in my mind.

17:17.444 --> 17:18.204
So why now?

17:18.224 --> 17:25.993
40 years, day after day, this man is put by the temple gates to beg for money.

17:26.394 --> 17:27.915
It was just his way of surviving.

17:28.956 --> 17:30.418
Day after day,

17:30.562 --> 17:37.870
He was placed there begging, and yet on this ordinary day, something happens in his life that changes him forever.

17:38.350 --> 17:39.311
Why today?

17:40.212 --> 18:00.434
And I sat there with this question looking for some deep answer, something beyond just, oh, well, in God's timing, because how many of you know when you're really wrestling with something, when you've been chained up and bound by something for so long, the last thing you want to hear as you're working to get free is just, oh, in God's timing, I want to be able to trust God's timing, but that's not the thing I want to hear all the time.

18:00.898 --> 18:09.466
And so I'm looking at this passage going, what was different about today, one day, every day, time of prayer, one day, every day, time of prayer?

18:09.987 --> 18:14.731
What was different about today that led to this God change in this man's life?

18:15.512 --> 18:17.794
And the answer is right on the surface.

18:19.175 --> 18:20.357
What was different about today?

18:20.397 --> 18:22.058
He met Peter.

18:24.420 --> 18:25.842
That's what was different about today.

18:26.623 --> 18:28.584
He met Peter.

18:29.706 --> 18:30.226
And y'all,

18:30.626 --> 18:32.248
The man's not the only one changing.

18:33.089 --> 18:34.070
Peter's changing too.

18:35.933 --> 18:43.883
And I realize that as Luke writes this story, the man who was healed that was lame from birth, he's not even the main character.

18:44.984 --> 18:45.505
Peter is.

18:46.626 --> 18:53.294
And Luke is trying to get us to see that Peter is changing as there's a whole bunch of transition happening.

18:53.535 --> 18:54.716
Let me give you some context.

18:54.836 --> 18:56.178
Luke wrote the gospel

18:56.258 --> 19:00.143
of Luke where he recorded the words and deeds that Jesus did on the earth.

19:00.523 --> 19:04.088
And then he continues his gospel of Luke with the book of Acts.

19:04.848 --> 19:10.095
Acts chapter one starts out with Jesus who has resurrected from the dead, ascending into heaven.

19:10.155 --> 19:13.038
So Luke's trying to get you to see there's a God change happening.

19:13.619 --> 19:20.427
Jesus who had been doing ministry on earth for three years has now resurrected and ascended to the Father.

19:20.728 --> 19:21.869
That's Acts chapter one.

19:22.670 --> 19:25.874
Acts chapter two, there's another God change that happened.

19:26.146 --> 19:32.315
as the apostles, the people who had been with Jesus during his earthly ministry are in an upper room in Jerusalem praying.

19:32.755 --> 19:41.047
God sends the Spirit, the Holy Spirit, and it falls on them like tongues of fire, and the church begins that day in Acts chapter two.

19:41.307 --> 19:42.509
Y'all, that's a God change.

19:44.131 --> 19:54.546
God is saying, although Jesus in his physical body has ascended into heaven, Luke wants us to know that the ministry of Jesus is now continuing, but it continues through his church.

19:55.394 --> 20:07.138
And then in Acts 3 where we are, Luke is trying to get you to see that not only is there so much change happening, but as the way God is working in the earth is changing, he's changing Peter 2.

20:07.559 --> 20:10.585
The Peter we read about in Acts 3.

20:11.026 --> 20:14.553
Y'all, if you read about him in the Gospels, this is not the same Peter.

20:16.036 --> 20:16.818
This Peter?

20:17.314 --> 20:19.700
in the name of Jesus Christ and Nazareth walk.

20:19.720 --> 20:26.096
But y'all, it wasn't too long ago, right now he's healing people, but not too long ago, he was cutting off someone's ear with a sword.

20:26.817 --> 20:28.722
How many of you know this is not the same Peter?

20:29.314 --> 20:41.908
This Peter here who's boldly declaring who Jesus is and what he's done, not too long ago, just weeks earlier, was keeping his distance as Jesus went to the cross and even denying that he knew him.

20:42.228 --> 20:43.790
This is not the same Peter.

20:44.090 --> 20:47.234
He's somewhere between Fisherman Peter and St. Peter.

20:47.334 --> 20:50.497
He's not there yet, but he's certainly not who he used to be.

20:50.557 --> 20:56.564
And a miracle takes place in this man's life because God is changing.

20:56.924 --> 20:58.546
Peter, Peter is going through.

20:58.658 --> 20:59.900
a God change right now.

21:00.500 --> 21:03.624
I want to show you a few things that are changing in Peter's life.

21:03.965 --> 21:04.886
The first one is this.

21:04.966 --> 21:08.531
It says that Peter looked straight at him as did John.

21:08.891 --> 21:11.995
Then Peter said, look at us.

21:12.756 --> 21:15.780
So the man gave him his attention, expecting to get something from him.

21:16.481 --> 21:21.548
It's amazing to me that before the man gave Peter his attention, Peter gave him his.

21:23.070 --> 21:23.891
Peter's changing.

21:24.972 --> 21:26.514
Because Peter had a tendency

21:26.626 --> 21:29.970
If you read about his life, to always be caught up in what he was doing.

21:30.570 --> 21:32.753
Always be caught up in his agenda.

21:33.173 --> 21:36.617
Always be focused on what's in it for Peter right now.

21:37.338 --> 21:43.404
And it's amazing that as Peter is doing his thing, going up to the temple to pray, it was the right thing to do.

21:43.725 --> 21:45.247
It was on his calendar for the day.

21:45.487 --> 21:46.868
I'm going to the temple to pray.

21:47.489 --> 21:55.698
It's amazing that Peter, as God is changing him, stops to see someone in their condition who needed help.

21:56.322 --> 21:59.546
The fact that Peter saw him is incredible.

22:00.007 --> 22:04.293
It lets me know that Peter is changing, because that's not like Peter.

22:04.333 --> 22:15.509
Now, when the scripture says that he saw him, it's an echo to when scripture uses the word saw, it's an indication of it means he was filled with compassion and a sense of responsibility.

22:16.109 --> 22:19.534
You know, this is Peter who would say, hey, tell the little children to get away from Jesus.

22:19.594 --> 22:20.556
I'm spending time with them.

22:20.896 --> 22:25.202
He's now filled with compassion and a sense of responsibility.

22:25.506 --> 22:32.935
Like when Jesus was about to raise a little boy from the dead, it says that he saw his mother in his heart went out for him.

22:32.955 --> 22:35.438
Jesus saw people and had compassion.

22:35.859 --> 22:41.465
And after three years of being with Jesus and not always getting it, now Peter is changing.

22:41.525 --> 22:44.689
And as he's going to the temple, he sees this man.

22:44.849 --> 22:49.615
Now, every day, thousands of people would have walked past this man.

22:50.236 --> 22:52.018
And many of them would have given him money.

22:52.226 --> 22:56.090
As they went to the temple, the worship, part of their worship was giving alms to the poor.

22:56.511 --> 22:58.533
So there would have been beggars all around the temple.

22:59.034 --> 23:03.859
And people as they would walk to the temple, they would walk past them and maybe throw them some money.

23:04.320 --> 23:07.043
They would look past them, but they wouldn't look at them.

23:08.124 --> 23:12.629
What's different about this is that Peter stops and he sees the man.

23:13.270 --> 23:15.493
He gives him his attention.

23:16.033 --> 23:18.616
Instead of just giving him money, this isn't transactional.

23:19.537 --> 23:20.338
It's relational.

23:21.794 --> 23:34.492
And one of the ways that I know God is changing me in my life is when I begin to see people, see people, not get so caught up in my world and what I have to do and what I think should happen.

23:35.133 --> 23:41.161
But I want God to give me eyes to see people for where they are and that he would fill me with compassion.

23:41.662 --> 23:43.564
I'm so glad Tad's sitting in church today.

23:43.584 --> 23:45.467
You're always in church, but I was glad you're here today.

23:46.048 --> 23:50.514
One of the things I love about Tad is this is one of the things I admire about Tad because

23:51.362 --> 24:00.112
Katie, when we do baptisms as a church and there's sometimes hundreds of people lining outside the tank waiting to get baptized, you can see them kind of shaky tears in their eyes.

24:00.192 --> 24:02.074
It's such a big and special moment for them.

24:02.715 --> 24:06.058
I love watching your husband because he has a way of seeing people.

24:07.079 --> 24:15.909
And Tad will walk through the line and stop and talk to each person and pray for every single person being baptized that day because he's a changed man.

24:16.810 --> 24:20.274
God saw him and now he sees others.

24:20.706 --> 24:32.059
I wonder what God might do through you if you become a person who has eyes to see people who are in need.

24:33.040 --> 24:35.463
That was a prayer I had for a year I'd wake up every day.

24:35.483 --> 24:40.689
It was simply one like this, God help me see Christ in others that they might see Christ in me.

24:41.330 --> 24:44.954
God help me see Christ in others that they might see Christ in me.

24:45.295 --> 24:48.018
See Peter, he's not seeing like he used to see.

24:48.290 --> 24:49.472
He's seeing like Jesus.

24:49.872 --> 24:52.637
He's noticing people in their need in their condition.

24:52.697 --> 24:59.247
And he senses not only compassion, not just, I feel for them, but I have a sense of responsibility to do something about it.

24:59.287 --> 25:00.329
And look what happens next.

25:00.369 --> 25:05.737
Not only does Peter see him, but Peter then says, silver or gold, I do not have.

25:06.739 --> 25:14.071
If anyone had an excuse just to walk by this man that day, it was Peter because he did not have what the man was asking for.

25:14.712 --> 25:16.274
He didn't have silver.

25:16.482 --> 25:16.983
our gold.

25:17.324 --> 25:22.396
And as this man is asking for money, Peter could have just been, nope, gone on his way.

25:22.977 --> 25:26.225
But he stops and he says, silver or gold, I do not have, but look at this.

25:26.586 --> 25:30.194
But what I do have, I give to you.

25:31.042 --> 25:36.628
I know Peter is changing because most of his life, Peter operated from a place of scarcity.

25:37.108 --> 25:45.217
Like when crowds of people were waiting around to hear Jesus, Peter's the one saying, send the crowds away so they can get something to eat because he himself was hungry.

25:45.477 --> 25:49.822
Peter had a way of just thinking about being protective, and yet here he is in this scenario.

25:50.242 --> 25:57.330
I know God is changing him because he says, I don't have what you're asking for, but what I do have, I want to give it to you.

25:57.922 --> 26:02.889
I know God is changing me when I begin to give more than what people ask for.

26:04.512 --> 26:11.242
If you can get this idea in your heart, I really believe it will unlock your ministry this year and the things that God wants to do through your life.

26:11.903 --> 26:16.530
So many of us live our lives going, well, if someone asks for it, I'll give it to them.

26:16.930 --> 26:32.174
But something fundamentally shifts in the way that God can use you when you stop limiting your ministry by what people are asking for, and you begin to look at God, what have you already given me in my life that I can give to be a blessing and make a difference in someone's life?

26:33.115 --> 26:37.242
Because you have to realize people will rarely ask you for what they actually need.

26:38.003 --> 26:39.585
They just ask you for what they want.

26:40.166 --> 26:42.991
This man, he wasn't asking for healing.

26:43.531 --> 26:45.234
He was asking for money.

26:46.050 --> 26:48.513
An example in my life, my friend Levi's here today.

26:48.533 --> 26:50.296
I didn't tell him I was going to use him as an example.

26:50.356 --> 26:54.341
But when we were getting to know each other, we'd hung out a couple of times through a mutual friend.

26:54.381 --> 26:57.245
And one day, that friend of ours, he pulls me aside privately.

26:57.265 --> 26:58.026
I've never told you this.

26:58.086 --> 27:01.952
And he said, Levi wants to go to church with you so bad.

27:01.972 --> 27:03.273
I said, what?

27:04.215 --> 27:05.797
And two things came through my mind.

27:05.997 --> 27:07.379
I said, all the times we've hung out.

27:07.439 --> 27:08.981
He's never asked me about going to church.

27:09.001 --> 27:09.682
What's up with that?

27:10.370 --> 27:11.972
And second of all, it's a church.

27:12.032 --> 27:13.794
He doesn't need a special invite to come.

27:13.854 --> 27:15.356
If he wants to come, he can just come.

27:15.376 --> 27:18.300
You don't need an invite from the campus pastor to show up here.

27:18.320 --> 27:19.041
But I thought about it.

27:19.061 --> 27:20.963
And I said, he said, no, he really wants to go with you.

27:21.063 --> 27:22.725
I bet if you ask him, he'll come.

27:23.226 --> 27:25.849
And so on his encouragement, I invited Levi to church.

27:25.869 --> 27:26.350
And guess what?

27:26.730 --> 27:27.111
He came.

27:27.611 --> 27:29.113
Now, this isn't a dramatic story.

27:29.133 --> 27:31.416
He already had a relationship with Christ.

27:31.876 --> 27:34.400
But he was outside of Christian community.

27:34.880 --> 27:36.762
And he didn't have a place of regular worship.

27:37.403 --> 27:38.064
And I knew that.

27:38.925 --> 27:39.666
And I knew that.

27:40.162 --> 27:46.289
And I knew I had what he needed, but I never offered it because he never asked.

27:47.871 --> 27:58.042
And I wonder if there are people in your life who need what you have, but you are withholding it because you're waiting for them to ask you.

27:59.003 --> 28:05.490
And I wonder, well, you're assuming, well, if they wanted to come to church with me, if they wanted me to pray with them, they would ask and they're going,

28:05.634 --> 28:06.215
I don't get it.

28:06.555 --> 28:07.597
I know they love their church.

28:07.677 --> 28:08.839
They talk about it all the time.

28:08.859 --> 28:09.880
They post the messages.

28:10.141 --> 28:11.743
They're always playing the worship song.

28:11.763 --> 28:15.609
I wonder how they love their church so much, and yet they've never asked me to come.

28:17.492 --> 28:21.358
My dad's here today, so I want to use him as an example, and it's a good one too, okay?

28:23.581 --> 28:34.898
But so often when I call my dad to talk to him, he'll tell me how he got to minister to someone, how he got to pray with someone, whether that's praying for someone, an employee at his office who

28:35.234 --> 28:39.719
Got a cancer diagnosis or someone at the gym who's going through a divorce.

28:40.420 --> 28:41.761
And you always call me with these stories.

28:41.781 --> 28:42.962
I got to pray for so-and-so.

28:42.982 --> 28:43.683
They're going through this.

28:43.723 --> 28:44.424
They're going through that.

28:44.764 --> 28:49.810
And I was always wondering, why are so many people asking my dad to pray for him, pray for them?

28:50.430 --> 28:54.615
Because, y'all, I'm a pastor and people don't even ask me to pray for them as often as they ask him.

28:55.255 --> 28:57.037
Time after time he tells me these stories.

28:57.057 --> 29:00.641
And then I realize no one's asking him to pray with them.

29:02.703 --> 29:05.106
No one's asking him to pray with them.

29:06.018 --> 29:10.804
But somewhere along the way, he decided to be intentional with what God has given him.

29:11.645 --> 29:15.050
And instead of waiting for someone to ask, he decided to give.

29:15.691 --> 29:23.441
So when someone said, I just got a diagnosis, he knows he can't heal their cancer, but he gave what he had.

29:24.142 --> 29:24.943
Can I pray for you?

29:25.564 --> 29:31.271
When someone's going through a divorce, he knows, I don't know how to fix your marriage right now, but can I pray for you?

29:31.732 --> 29:33.394
He gave what he had.

29:33.858 --> 29:38.943
And I want to let you know, brothers and sisters, that God has given you so much.

29:39.684 --> 29:45.770
And what God has done in your life is not just meant for you, it's meant for other people around you.

29:46.150 --> 29:53.817
There are people in your world who need the peace you have, who need the joy you have, who need the hope you have, who need the strength you have.

29:54.218 --> 29:55.599
And God has given it to you.

29:55.859 --> 29:59.963
God has changed you so that you can give it to them.

30:00.003 --> 30:02.866
Peter says, silver or gold, I don't have.

30:03.074 --> 30:05.237
But what I do have, I give to you.

30:05.277 --> 30:09.021
He gave the man something so much greater than what he asked for.

30:09.582 --> 30:13.907
And that's my heart, heart for this year, not only for myself, but for all of us as a church.

30:14.228 --> 30:23.799
What would this city look like if we became a people who did not wait to be asked, but decided that we're gonna freely give what God has given us.

30:25.321 --> 30:26.102
He gave what he had.

30:26.142 --> 30:30.988
Look at this last thing that's changing in Peter's life and it shows up in this powerful statement.

30:31.769 --> 30:32.690
He says next,

30:32.898 --> 30:38.225
In the name of Jesus of Nazareth, walk.

30:38.245 --> 30:40.488
Y'all, this is a change for Peter too.

30:41.490 --> 30:46.056
Now, sometimes when we read these stories, it's easy for us to kind of strip the humanity out of it.

30:46.116 --> 30:47.898
Sometimes Peter sounds so bold.

30:47.958 --> 30:50.682
In the name of Jesus Christ of Nazareth, walk.

30:51.403 --> 30:58.032
But I wonder, do you think maybe underneath the surface, Peter's heart was racing a little bit?

30:58.753 --> 31:02.738
Do you think maybe as he said, in the name of Jesus Christ, walk that his voice

31:03.106 --> 31:10.476
got a little bit shaky, wondering, man, I've seen Jesus do miracles before, but what if this doesn't work?

31:10.956 --> 31:12.078
There's all these people around.

31:12.098 --> 31:14.802
What if I say, get up in the name of Jesus and this man can't?

31:15.142 --> 31:15.943
What if it doesn't work?

31:15.983 --> 31:17.065
What if he can't walk?

31:17.085 --> 31:20.669
Worse, what if I set him up to hope again and it doesn't work?

31:21.310 --> 31:28.740
I wonder if Peter was feeling a little bit anxious as he walked past this man and decided that day I'm gonna pray for his healing.

31:29.581 --> 31:33.106
Maybe he was a little bit anxious or the old Peter certainly would have been

31:33.346 --> 31:34.188
arrogant, you know?

31:34.549 --> 31:36.293
Peter had a way of just doing things his way.

31:36.373 --> 31:37.135
I know what's best.

31:38.118 --> 31:42.909
But whether it's insecurity or conceitedness, it's all self-consciousness.

31:43.892 --> 31:51.410
And one of the changes that God wants to bring about in our life is taking us from being self-conscious to Christ-conscious.

31:52.482 --> 31:59.271
When he says in the name of Jesus, this is not just like a formality, like what you pray at the end of giving a blessing over your food.

31:59.551 --> 32:00.432
Thank you for these carrots.

32:00.452 --> 32:03.496
Thank you for this chicken blessed to our bodies in the name of Jesus, amen.

32:03.516 --> 32:03.977
No, no, no.

32:04.518 --> 32:17.234
When he says in the name of Jesus, it means that he is walking in the identity of Jesus, the power of Jesus, and the authority of Jesus.

32:17.602 --> 32:26.167
So as Peter stands before this man, this is a change for Peter because for once in his life, he's not trying to do it in his own strength.

32:26.187 --> 32:32.626
He's doing it in the strength and in the name and in the authority and in the power of Jesus.

32:35.394 --> 32:44.644
Some of us talk ourselves out of being used by God because we're going, how can I give someone advice on how to fix a relationship when there's people I'm afraid to pick up the phone and call?

32:44.924 --> 32:49.329
How am I gonna talk to someone about their addiction when I've got this plank in my own eye?

32:49.589 --> 32:55.856
And so we disqualify ourselves from being used by God because we think, how can God use someone like me?

32:56.156 --> 33:01.522
But the reality is that if you are in Christ, it has nothing to do with your worst days,

33:01.602 --> 33:08.750
or your best days, when you stand up in front of someone to minister or to be used, you're not doing it in your name.

33:09.250 --> 33:13.315
You're doing it in the name of Jesus.

33:15.357 --> 33:16.478
You have His power.

33:17.139 --> 33:18.420
You have His authority.

33:18.460 --> 33:20.282
You're doing it in His name.

33:20.743 --> 33:24.747
You know, yesterday, Anna said to me, she said, you try to be nicer to me before you preach.

33:24.807 --> 33:27.190
I think she said, are you being so nice lately?

33:27.210 --> 33:31.154
It's like I need to come up here with a clear conscience.

33:31.298 --> 33:34.242
I said in my head, I thought, well, it's better than the alternative, right?

33:34.843 --> 33:38.548
Because not too long ago, I used to be so mean before I preached.

33:38.928 --> 33:39.589
Wouldn't that be mean?

33:39.869 --> 33:43.754
I can't believe I'm telling them this right now.

33:43.774 --> 33:52.886
And honestly, for a long time, it was the pressure and the anxiety I would feel around preaching because I would think, what do I have to say?

33:53.848 --> 33:55.570
What do I have authority to speak on?

33:56.551 --> 33:58.674
Who am I to stand up there and talk to people?

33:59.714 --> 34:08.785
And through the work of God in my life, something began to shift where all that anxiety started to go away because I realized it's not me standing here.

34:09.906 --> 34:14.492
That when God gives me an opportunity to minister, I'm not doing it as Jonathan Joseph's.

34:15.293 --> 34:17.215
I'm here to minister in the name of Jesus.

34:19.658 --> 34:23.803
So it's not, it's not about what I have to say.

34:24.624 --> 34:26.066
It's about what he has to say.

34:26.690 --> 34:31.114
And it's not about my worthiness, whether I was mean or whether I was nice, but I'm glad I'm being nice now.

34:32.315 --> 34:33.116
It's not about that.

34:33.717 --> 34:34.798
It's about what he's done.

34:34.838 --> 34:36.920
It's about what he did.

34:37.901 --> 34:53.655
Peter looks at the man and says, in the name of Jesus Christ of Nazareth, walk and instantly the man's healed and he gets to his feet and he's jumping and he's leaping and he's praising God because on this ordinary day, something changed.

34:54.336 --> 34:56.338
He met Peter and Peter's

34:56.578 --> 34:57.339
a changed man.

34:58.721 --> 35:02.085
There are things that God will do in your life that aren't just meant for you.

35:03.466 --> 35:04.648
They're meant for other people too.

35:04.828 --> 35:07.391
God changes you so that he can change others.

35:08.453 --> 35:08.973
And look at this.

35:09.073 --> 35:16.002
As people are standing looking at this man in wonder and amazement, it says that a bunch of people start to come together.

35:16.042 --> 35:18.385
The words getting out about what has happened.

35:18.966 --> 35:20.648
And in verse 12, look what Peter says.

35:21.429 --> 35:22.610
When Peter saw this,

35:22.754 --> 35:26.920
He said to the crowd, he uses every miracle as an opportunity to declare the gospel.

35:27.982 --> 35:32.348
When Peter saw this, he said to them, fellow Israelites, why does this surprise you?

35:33.209 --> 35:40.881
Why do you stare at us as if it's by our own power or godliness we had made this man walk?

35:41.622 --> 35:42.563
Look at verse 16.

35:43.545 --> 35:50.054
By faith in the name of Jesus, this man whom you see and know was made strong.

35:50.856 --> 35:52.498
It is in Jesus' name.

35:52.834 --> 35:59.843
and the faith that comes through Him that has completely healed Him as you all can see.

36:01.405 --> 36:04.689
It is in Jesus' name and the faith that comes through Him.

36:05.671 --> 36:07.894
Peter said, what are you looking at us for?

36:07.954 --> 36:10.497
It's not by our power.

36:10.938 --> 36:11.739
It's not by might.

36:12.560 --> 36:14.843
It's by the power of Jesus that this man can walk.

36:14.963 --> 36:18.447
Not only Jesus' name, but He says by faith in the name of Jesus.

36:18.507 --> 36:20.530
Now the question is, who's faith?

36:22.146 --> 36:25.330
whose faith in Jesus healed this man?

36:25.370 --> 36:28.933
This man never asked to be healed.

36:29.574 --> 36:30.395
It wasn't his faith.

36:31.336 --> 36:34.199
There's no indication this man even knew who Jesus was.

36:35.220 --> 36:36.141
It wasn't his faith.

36:36.882 --> 36:38.924
So whose faith in Jesus?

36:40.526 --> 36:40.927
Peters.

36:45.031 --> 36:47.114
Your faith isn't just meant to change you.

36:49.036 --> 36:51.218
Your faith is meant to change others.

37:00.706 --> 37:05.090
And some of us are in the habit of just coming to church when we need something from God.

37:05.110 --> 37:06.131
I got to get to church today.

37:06.191 --> 37:07.112
I need encouragement.

37:07.513 --> 37:08.213
I need strength.

37:08.834 --> 37:17.563
And as long as you look at your faith that way as if it's just for you to help you get through and to help you get by, you always limit what God can do through your life.

37:18.684 --> 37:28.914
But what if you decided that, hey, I'm coming to church anyway because even though I might not have a need today, maybe there's someone else coming to church that needs a touch from God.

37:29.122 --> 37:31.866
And maybe God has given me what they need.

37:32.707 --> 37:35.011
Your faith isn't just meant to change you.

37:35.051 --> 37:38.135
It's meant to change the people around you.

37:39.117 --> 37:44.244
And Luke goes on to say that there are many, many people who place their faith in Jesus that day.

37:44.285 --> 37:48.030
People's lives were changed because God changed that man.

37:48.671 --> 37:52.176
But God changed that man because he changed Peter.

37:54.059 --> 37:56.082
And I see this year being different for you.

37:56.450 --> 38:00.315
Because I know all of us have things in our life that we're saying, God, just help me believe.

38:00.356 --> 38:01.397
I want to expect you.

38:01.998 --> 38:03.340
I want to have expectation.

38:03.400 --> 38:04.201
I want to have faith.

38:04.221 --> 38:04.922
I want to have hope.

38:04.962 --> 38:05.803
I want to have trust.

38:05.823 --> 38:08.187
There are things in my life that I want to see God change.

38:08.207 --> 38:13.414
But I have to remember, too, that some of the things that God wants to change in my life aren't just meant for me.

38:13.454 --> 38:16.859
It's because God has blessed me to be a blessing.

38:17.460 --> 38:20.123
God changes me so that he can change others.

38:20.504 --> 38:21.706
I need eyes to see.

38:21.726 --> 38:24.850
I need open hands to give what he's given me.

38:25.410 --> 38:26.951
And I don't do it in my own strength.

38:27.432 --> 38:28.693
I do it in the name of Jesus.

38:29.554 --> 38:35.580
I see this year being a year where you go from just coming to God like Peter used to do.

38:35.920 --> 38:39.604
So much of Peter's life was following Jesus because of what was in it for him.

38:40.224 --> 38:41.566
And now Peter's changing.

38:42.607 --> 38:43.427
Peter's changing.

38:44.068 --> 38:49.393
And he sees his purpose in life, not just knowing Jesus for his own sake, but for the sake of others.

38:49.773 --> 38:51.575
I see this changing in your life this year.

38:51.935 --> 38:54.578
I see you coming to church, not just to receive,

38:54.658 --> 38:55.299
but to give.

38:55.880 --> 39:01.008
I see you praying for people out in the lobby after church because you saw an orange Bible in their hand.

39:01.449 --> 39:02.670
And you said, I can pray for them.

39:02.771 --> 39:04.393
I can give them a word of encouragement.

39:04.794 --> 39:13.187
I see you looking at someone in worship and God giving of Scripture on your heart and you going up to them and being a blessing to them because your faith is not just for you.

39:13.327 --> 39:16.672
God changes you so that he can change others.

39:18.655 --> 39:20.338
So I want to close by just

39:21.922 --> 39:25.588
praying over you a prayer of activation today as we head into this new year.

39:27.170 --> 39:34.442
That this would be a year that not only do you see God changes in your own life, but that God would change people through you as well.

39:34.542 --> 39:35.564
Can you stand to your feet?

39:47.323 --> 39:48.144
And let's do it like this.

39:48.184 --> 39:49.266
Let's put our hand on,

39:49.890 --> 39:52.072
the shoulder of someone around us right now.

39:52.993 --> 40:01.543
And in the spirit of this message, I'm gonna pray, and you're gonna repeat after me, and I haven't planned this out, so there's not like a nice cadence to it.

40:02.083 --> 40:03.064
You just gotta go with me.

40:05.187 --> 40:11.493
But you're gonna pray for the person on your right and on your left, because you have been given the spirit of God, and you are in Christ.

40:11.553 --> 40:15.117
The Bible says that the prayers of the righteous are powerful and effective.

40:16.259 --> 40:19.442
And God is getting ready to do incredible things in our church this year.

40:20.034 --> 40:25.581
God is getting ready to do amazing things in your life, things that will exceed your wildest imagination.

40:26.282 --> 40:29.947
But it's not just what he wants to do in you, it's what he wants to do through you.

40:30.989 --> 40:38.659
So with your hand on the shoulders of the people next to you, do your best to flow with me as we say this prayer together, okay?

40:38.979 --> 40:45.428
I said, Father, I thank you for the person on my right and on my left.

40:45.448 --> 40:46.930
Thank you for what you've done in them.

40:48.674 --> 40:50.457
Thank you for what you're going to do in them.

40:52.720 --> 40:55.124
And I thank you for what you wanna do through them.

40:57.347 --> 40:59.310
I pray that you would give them boldness this year.

41:01.474 --> 41:12.210
I pray that you would open up their eyes to see the opportunities that you're giving them to make a difference for your glory.

41:13.733 --> 41:14.434
Strengthen them.

41:15.615 --> 41:17.298
Increase their expectation.

41:18.626 --> 41:24.413
stir up their faith that we would see you move like never before.

41:25.755 --> 41:31.002
We pray these things in the name of Jesus.

41:32.023 --> 41:33.004
Let's give God a praise.

41:39.733 --> 41:41.495
Hey, I hope you enjoyed the podcast.

41:41.555 --> 41:43.858
And if you did, make sure to share it.

41:43.970 --> 41:48.656
and subscribe so we can get you all of these new messages as soon as they're available.

41:49.237 --> 41:52.741
I also want to take a moment and thank all of you who are a part of Elevation.

41:53.222 --> 42:01.972
Whether you support us financially or serve with us or just share these messages, it's because of you that we're able to reach people all around the world.

42:02.353 --> 42:08.080
And if you want more information on how to be a part of Elevation, click the link in the description.

42:08.581 --> 42:09.522
Thanks again for listening.

42:09.542 --> 42:12.946
Make sure to leave a review, share the message and subscribe.

42:13.154 --> 42:14.067
God bless you.

